honeywell.printer

Class DocumentDPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.Document
      • honeywell.printer.DocumentDPL

  • public class DocumentDPL
extends Document
    This class handles the interface between the printer and the user application that wishes to use an Datamax-O'Neil DPL printer.

    These functions can be used to 'build' a document using abstract methods instead of the raw 'DPL' mode commands. The DocumentDPL class is designed when exact placement of items is desired.

      • writeBarCodePDF417

        public void writeBarCodePDF417(java.lang.String textString,
                               boolean isTruncated,
                               int securityLevel,
                               int aspectRatio,
                               int dataRows,
                               int dataCols,
                               int row,
                               int col,
                               ParametersDPL parameters)
        This function will print the provided text to the document as a PDF417 2D barcode using the provided printing parameter values.
        Parameters:
        textString - Data to be encoded
        isTruncated - Specifies a normal or truncated bar code
        securityLevel - 1-digit security level ranging from 0 to 8
        aspectRatio - 2-digit aspect ratio specified as a fraction, with first digit being numerator and second digit the denominator. Use "00" for default ratio of 1:2. Valid range is from "00" to "99".
        dataRows - 2-digit number specifying number of rows requested. Valid range 3-90. Default value = 0 to let printer find best fit
        dataCols - 2-digit number specifying number of cols requested. Valid range 1-30. Default value = 0 to let printer find best fit
        row - Row position, starting from zero, to start printing at.
        col - Column position, starting from zero, to start printing at.
        parameters - Parameters DPL object to specify other printing properties

      • writeBarCodeDataMatrix

        public void writeBarCodeDataMatrix(java.lang.String textString,
                                   int correctionLevel,
                                   int digitFormatID,
                                   int rowsRequested,
                                   int colsRequested,
                                   int row,
                                   int col,
                                   ParametersDPL parameters)
        This function prints a DataMatrix Bar Code, a 2-D matrix symbology comprised of square mdoules arranged within a perimeter finder pattern.

        Two basic types:

        ECC 000-140

        ECC 200

        Parameters:
        textString - Any 8-byte data
        correctionLevel - 3-Digit convolutional error correction level(ECC).Valid values: 0,50,80,100,140,200
        digitFormatID - 1-digit format Identification:

        0 - Automatically choose encodation scheme base on characters to be encoded

        1 - Numeric

        2 - Uppercase alphabetic

        3 - Uppercase alphanumeric and punctuation characters(.,-/)

        4 - Uppercase alphanumeric

        5 - ASCII,the full 128 ASCII char set

        6 - Any 8-bit byte

        For ECC 200, value should be 0

        rowsRequested - Odd or even number of rows requested. Valid Values:

        0 - Automatically determined

        For ECC 000-140: 9, 11, 13,..49

        For ECC 200: 10,12,14,16,1,20,22,24,26,32,36,40,44,48,52,64,72,80,96,104,120,132,144

        colsRequested - Odd or even number of cols requested. Valid Values:

        0 - Automatically determined

        For ECC 000-140: 0 , 9, 11, 13,..49

        For ECC 200: 10,12,14,16,1,20,22,24,26,32,36,40,44,48,52,64,72,80,96,104,120,132,144

        row - Row position, starting from zero, to start printing at.
        col - Column position, starting from zero, to start printing at.
        parameters - Parameters DPL object to specify other printing properties

      • writeBarCodeQRCode

        public void writeBarCodeQRCode(java.lang.String textString,
                               boolean autoFormatting,
                               int QRCodeModel,
                               java.lang.String correctionLevel,
                               java.lang.String maskNumber,
                               java.lang.String inputMode,
                               java.lang.String charMode,
                               int row,
                               int col,
                               ParametersDPL parameters)
        This prints a QRCode Bar Code.
        Parameters:
        textString - Numeric Data, Alphanumeric Data, 8-bit byte data, and Kanji characters
        autoFormatting - Specifies to use auto or manual QR bar code formatting.If this is true, other parameters will be ignored.
        QRCodeModel - QR Code Model number, optional. Model 2 is default
        correctionLevel - Error Correction Levels:

        "H" = Ultra Reliability Level (30%)

        "Q" = High Reliability Level (25%)

        "M" = Standard Reliability Level (15%)

        "L" = High Density Level (7%)

        maskNumber - Mask Number,optional:

        None = Auto

        0-7 = Mask 0 to Mask 7

        8 = No Mask

        inputMode - Data Input Mode:

        A = Auto, ASCII

        a = Auto,hex-ASCII

        M = Manual, ASCII

        m = Manual, hex-ASCII

        charMode - Character Mode:

        N = Numeric

        A = Alphanumeric

        B = Binary (where nnnn = data bytecount,4 decimal digits; byte-count /2 for hex-ASCII)

        K = Kanji

        row - Row position, starting from zero, to start printing at.
        col - Column position, starting from zero, to start printing at.
        parameters - Parameters DPL object to specify other printing properties

      • writeBarCodeAztec

        public void writeBarCodeAztec(java.lang.String textString,
                              int textLength,
                              boolean ECIMode,
                              int errorCorrection,
                              int row,
                              int col,
                              ParametersDPL parameters)
        This prints an Aztec Bar code.
        Parameters:
        textString - ALl ASCII characters, depending on selected options
        textLength - Optional string length specifier. Set to 0 if not used
        ECIMode - Extended Channel Interpretation mode; 0 = Disabled, 1 = Enabled
        errorCorrection - Error Correction(EC)/Amount:

        0:Default

        1-99: EC fixed value,expressed as percent

        101-104: Compact Core, 1 to 4 layers

        201-232: Full size core,1 to 32 layers

        300:Rune format, encodes 3 ASCII 0-256 decimal digits.

        row - Row position, starting from zero, to start printing at.
        col - Column position, starting from zero, to start printing at.
        parameters - Parameters DPL object to specify other printing properties

      • writeBarCodeGS1DataBar

        public void writeBarCodeGS1DataBar(java.lang.String primaryData,
                                   java.lang.String compositeData,
                                   java.lang.String GS1Type,
                                   int pixelMultiplier,
                                   int xPixelUndercut,
                                   int yPixelUndercut,
                                   int segmentsPerRow,
                                   int row,
                                   int col,
                                   ParametersDPL parameters)
        This function will print a GS1 DataBar barcode using the provided printing parameter values.
        Parameters:
        primaryData - Numeric linear data(length 13) or ISO646 character set(GS1 Expanded)

        Valid input data:

        GS1 Barcode TypeValid InputsNotes
        GS1 Truncated0-913-Digit EAN.UCC item ID number with linear symbol. Encodable character set 09. Maximum numeric data capacity is the application identifier plus 14-digit. Error detection is mod 79 checksum
        GS1 Stacked/Stacked Omnidirectional0-913-Digit EAN.UCC item ID number with linear symbol. Encodable character set 09. Maximum numeric data capacity is the application identifier plus 14-digit. Error detection is mod 79 checksum
        GS1 Limited0-913-Digit EAN.UCC item ID number with 0 or 1 within linear symbol. Encodable character set 09. Data must begin with 0 or 1. Error detection is mod 89 checksum
        GS1 Expanded0-9A-Za-z!%"&'(*+,-./:;<=>?14-Digit EAN.UCC item ID number plus supp. AI element strings. Encodable character set ISO 646(alphanumeric,20 punctuation characters, and FNC1). Maximum numeric data capacity is 74 numeric or 41 alphanumeric. Error detection is mod 211 checksum
        compositeData - Additional 2-D data

        Valid input data: All alphanumerics

        GS1Type - GS1 DataBar Barcode type:
        ValueDescription
        EGS1 DataBar Expanded

      • rightPad

        public static java.lang.String rightPad(java.lang.String str,
                                        int size,
                                        char padChar)

        Right pad a String with a specified character.

        The String is padded to the size of size.

         StringUtils.rightPad(null, *, *)     = null
 StringUtils.rightPad("", 3, 'z')     = "zzz"
 StringUtils.rightPad("bat", 3, 'z')  = "bat"
 StringUtils.rightPad("bat", 5, 'z')  = "batzz"
 StringUtils.rightPad("bat", 1, 'z')  = "bat"
 StringUtils.rightPad("bat", -1, 'z') = "bat"
        Parameters:
        str - the String to pad out, may be null
        size - the size to pad to
        padChar - the character to pad with
        Returns:
        right padded String or original String if no padding is necessary, null if null String input
        Since:
        2.0

      • rightPad

        public static java.lang.String rightPad(java.lang.String str,
                                        int size,
                                        java.lang.String padStr)

        Right pad a String with a specified String.

        The String is padded to the size of size.

         StringUtils.rightPad(null, *, *)      = null
 StringUtils.rightPad("", 3, "z")      = "zzz"
 StringUtils.rightPad("bat", 3, "yz")  = "bat"
 StringUtils.rightPad("bat", 5, "yz")  = "batyz"
 StringUtils.rightPad("bat", 8, "yz")  = "batyzyzy"
 StringUtils.rightPad("bat", 1, "yz")  = "bat"
 StringUtils.rightPad("bat", -1, "yz") = "bat"
 StringUtils.rightPad("bat", 5, null)  = "bat  "
 StringUtils.rightPad("bat", 5, "")    = "bat  "
        Parameters:
        str - the String to pad out, may be null
        size - the size to pad to
        padStr - the String to pad with, null or empty treated as single space
        Returns:
        right padded String or original String if no padding is necessary, null if null String input
